x4freetext: Electron linear accelerator
the authors also used transmission method
lower-level discriminator
The target was composed, of 10 Ta plates with
a diam. of 4.9 cm and an effective thickness of 7.4 cm
There was a 0.15 cm water gap between Ta plates in
order to cool the target effectively. The housing of
the target was made of titanium. This target was set
at the center of a cylindrical water moderator
contained in an aluminum cylinder with thickness of
0.5 cm, a diam. of 30 cm and height of 30 cm.
A natural Dy metal plate, 10 cmx 10 cm in area by
0.5 mm (0.001585 atoms/bar) in thickness, was used
as a transmission sample. The purity of the natural
Dy sample was better than 99.9%. A set of notch filters
of Co, Ta, and Cd plates with 0.5 mm, 0.2 mm, and
0.5 mm in thickness respectively, used for the
background measurement and the energy calibration.
A 6Li-ZnS(Ag) scintillator BC702 with a diam.
of 127 mm and a thickness of 6.35 mm mounted on an
EMI-93090 photomultiplier was used as a detector for
the neutron TOF spectrum measurement. Scintillator
consists of a matrix of a lithium compound enriched to
95% 6Li dispersed in a fine ZnS(Ag) phosphor powder.
SAMMY code (Reich-Moore approximation in the
application of R-matrix formalizm) was used to fit
the transmission data.
Data received from Dr. G.Kim for Subent 002,
resonance parameters were taken from Tbl.1 of Ann.Nucl.
Entry approved by Dr. G.Kim
Only considered the statistical errors for the
measurements because the other sources of uncertainties
which include the detection efficiencies,the geometric
factor for the sample, and the other systematic errors,
are negligible.
